	   <tr><td colspan=2>Our Sai experts state that the Sai are 1hb weapons.&nbsp;&nbsp;I accept that.<br>They also say they weigh a bit, in order to be strong enough to entangle, and hopefully break, an opponents sword, they should weigh some--accept this one is magical.<br>Many magical weapons weigh less than their normal counter parts--thats Magic.<br>This is a Lore item, meaning you can only have one.  That is not to say you can't use two sai's.  It means only one of them can be this particular Sai.  (You can't weild two Excaliburs since there is only one).  <br>The down side is that EQ needs more Sai, magical and mundane, so when we monks do our Instill DOubt Katta, we look goooood.<br>&nbsp;<br>ChiaPetz the Monkeyish Monk</td></tr>
