	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, they can be used very effectively to &quot;pierce&quot; even without a sharpened point. I have been &quot;stabbed&quot; by a blunt one, and omg that hurt bad, real bad. The pain is not a sharp pain, feels more like getting shot with a bullet proof vest on, only it hurts more and for longer. Stabbing with a dull point, or with something like a bo staff is not a fun thing, as the area is deeply bruised and swollen for days on end,and can possibly break bones depending on location and strength of the blow. Thus, making it highly effective for combat situations in RL where killing someone is not a good option, but rendering them in alot of pain and disabling them is.<br>&nbsp;<br>Reality is the fantasy world in which we live - J. Tracy<br>Vymdraven-Dark Elf Wizard<br>Bertox<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573242" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573242</a></td></tr>
