	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9941148984922><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6287&mid=9941148984922>Use of Sai</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6287&mid=9941148984922#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=32805><span id= >Gartha</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>67 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 2nd 7:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Anyone who has sai with points either put a point on them on their own, or bought them from a catalog which got them from a weaponmaking firm which didn't know it's business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sai are used for bludgeoning only as a secondary use, so they ought not even have a great damage rating, probably 2, 3 at the outside.  Sai were initially used by ninja or anyone who felt they might be facing an opponent armed with a sword or other bladed weapon.  It was rediculously simple for a skilled user to catch and break the blade of all but the finest quality katana (and not many were that great) rendering their opponent defenseless, after which the sai were used to deliver a knockout blow(s).  An animated turtle is not a very good source for historical fact.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
