	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, from what I understand about martial arts, sais are defensive weapons meant to deflect blows.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are no piercing weapons because piercing motions leave one open to attack.  These would be used much like parrying daggers...deflecting the blows of swords, even catching them leaving the attacker open for attack, probably by bashing them in with the blunt end of the sai.<br><br>I agree with the 1hb...they look like piercers, but that's not how they're used.<br>&nbsp;<br>--Wolfran Funkenstein</td></tr>
